Brecon RFC.label: Brecon RFC
Brecon RFC.description: Brecon Rugby Football Club is a rugby union club from the town of Brecon, Mid Wales. The club is a member of the Welsh Rugby Union and is a feeder club for the Cardiff Blues. Wikipedia

Crymych RFC.label: Crymych RFC
Crymych RFC.description: Crymych Rugby Football Club is a rugby union team from the village of Crymych in West Wales. The club is a member of the Welsh Rugby Union and is a feeder club for the Llanelli Scarlets. Wikipedia

Glamorgan County RFC.label: Glamorgan County RFC
Glamorgan County RFC.description: Glamorgan County RFC is a Welsh rugby union club that manages an invitational team, known as Glamorgan that originally played rugby at county level. Wikipedia

Edinburgh University RFC.label: Edinburgh University RFC
Edinburgh University RFC.description: Edinburgh University Rugby Football Club is a leading rugby union side based in Edinburgh, Scotland which currently plays its fixtures in the Edinburgh Regional Shield competition and the British Universities Premiership. Wikipedia

Oakdale RFC.label: Oakdale RFC
Oakdale RFC.description: Oakdale Rugby Football Club is a rugby union team from the village of Oakdale near Blackwood in Wales. The club is a member of the Welsh Rugby Union, and is a feeder club for the Newport Gwent Dragons. Wikipedia

Midleton RFC.label: Midleton RFC
Midleton RFC.description: Midleton RFC is an Irish rugby union club that currently plays in Division 2A of the All-Ireland League. Wikipedia

North Derbyshire Chargers.label: North Derbyshire Chargers
North Derbyshire Chargers.description: North Derbyshire Chargers RLFC are a rugby league club who play in the Midlands Rugby League at open age and junior level. Shortly after formation a merger was agreed with the Chesterfield Spires club. Wikipedia

Falmouth RFC.label: Falmouth RFC
Falmouth RFC.description: Falmouth RFC is a rugby union club based in the town of Falmouth, Cornwall, in the United Kingdom. The club plays at the Recreation Ground. Wikipedia

Ystalyfera RFC.label: Ystalyfera RFC
Ystalyfera RFC.description: Ystalyfera Rugby Football Club are a Welsh rugby union club based in Ystalyfera in south Wales. The club is a member of the Welsh Rugby Union and is also a feeder club for the Ospreys. Wikipedia

Denver Barbarians RFC.label: Denver Barbarians RFC
Denver Barbarians RFC.description: The Denver Barbarians Rugby Football Club is a SuperLeague rugby union and Division I team based in Denver, Colorado. Wikipedia

Boland Cavaliers.label: Boland Cavaliers
Boland Cavaliers.description: The Boland Cavaliers, are a South African rugby union team that participates in the annual Currie Cup tournament. Wikipedia

Eastern Province Kings.label: Eastern Province Kings
Eastern Province Kings.description: The Eastern Province Kings are a South African rugby union team that participates in the annual Currie Cup and Vodacom Cup competitions. They are governed by the Eastern Province Rugby Union. Wikipedia

Griffons (rugby team).label: Griffons
Griffons (rugby team).description: The Northern Free State Griffons are a South African rugby union team that participates in the annual Currie Cup and Vodacom Cup tournaments. Wikipedia

Coca Cola West Red Sparks.label: Coca Cola West Red Sparks
Coca Cola West Red Sparks.description: Coca Cola West Red Sparks RFC is a Japanese company-owned rugby union team based in Fukuoka city, Kyūshū. The coach is currently Shogo Mukai, the former Japan national rugby union team coach during the 2003 Rugby Union World Cup. Wikipedia

Lane Cove Rugby.label: Lane Cove Rugby
Lane Cove Rugby.description: Lane Cove Rugby Union Football Club is a rugby union club founded in 1949 and which participates in the New South Wales Suburban Rugby Union competition. The club is situated in Lane Cove in Sydney, New South Wales, Australia. Wikipedia

Honda Heat.label: Honda Heat
Honda Heat.description:
Honda Heat is a Japanese rugby union team based in Suzuka City, Mie Prefecture, Japan. The owner of the club is Honda Motor.
They play in the Top League, the top tier of the Japan's rugby union hierarchy. Wikipedia

Manly RUFC.label: Manly RUFC
Manly RUFC.description: Manly Rugby Union Football Club is a rugby union club based in Manly, a suburb of Sydney, New South Wales. The club was formed in 1906 and competes in the New South Wales Rugby Union competitions, the Shute Shield and Tooheys New Cup. Wikipedia

Leopards (rugby team).label: Leopards
Leopards (rugby team).description: The Leopards are a South African rugby union team that participates in the annual Currie Cup tournament, currently playing in the First Division. Their home ground is Olën Park in Potchefstroom. Wikipedia

NEC Green Rockets.label: NEC Green Rockets
NEC Green Rockets.description: NEC Green Rockets is a Japanese rugby union team in the Top League. The team's captain is Ryota Asano. The previous captain was Takuro Miuchi, who is currently the captain of the Japan national rugby union team. Wikipedia

Penrith Emus Rugby.label: Penrith Emus Rugby
Penrith Emus Rugby.description: Penrith Rugby Club, known as the Emus, are an Australian rugby union club based in Penrith, a western suburb of Sydney, New South Wales. The club competes in the New South Wales Rugby Union competitions, the Shute Shield and Tooheys New Cup. Wikipedia

Randwick DRUFC.label: Randwick DRUFC
Randwick DRUFC.description: Randwick District Rugby Union Football Club, also known as the Galloping Greens, is an Australian rugby union club which competes in the Sydney grade competition. Wikipedia

Ricoh Black Rams.label: Ricoh Black Rams
Ricoh Black Rams.description:
Ricoh Black Rams is a Japanese rugby union team in the Top League. Placed 10th in the 2004-5 season which meant it had to win a play-off against one of the top regional teams to stay in the league, as it did.
Slogan for 2006 season TAFU. Wikipedia

Secom Rugguts.label: Secom Rugguts
Secom Rugguts.description: Secom Rugguts is a Japanese rugby union team which was in the Top League for the first season of the league but was demoted at the end of the season. Wikipedia

Southern Kings.label: Southern Kings
Southern Kings.description: The Southern Kings are a rugby union team based in Port Elizabeth, South Africa who competed in the 2013 Super Rugby competition. Wikipedia

Suntory Sungoliath.label: Suntory Sungoliath
Suntory Sungoliath.description: Suntory Sungoliath is owned by the Suntory beverage company and is one of the Japanese rugby union teams in the Top League. The team is based in Fuchū, Tokyo, as is their local rival Toshiba Brave Lupus. Wikipedia

Toshiba Brave Lupus.label: Toshiba Brave Lupus
Toshiba Brave Lupus.description: Toshiba Brave Lupus is a Japanese rugby union team in the Top League. They are based in Fuchu, Tokyo, as is their local rival Suntory Sungoliath. Wikipedia

Toyota Verblitz.label: Toyota Verblitz
Toyota Verblitz.description: Toyota Verblitz is a Japanese rugby union team in the Top League. Verblitz is a conflation of verde and blitz. Wikipedia

World Fighting Bull.label: World Fighting Bull
World Fighting Bull.description: World Fighting Bull is a Top League team but was demoted at the end of the Top League fourth season. It is from Kobe in the Kansai area of Japan, and therefore a local rival of Kobe Steel Kobelco Steelers. Wikipedia

Yamaha Júbilo.label: Yamaha Júbilo
Yamaha Júbilo.description: Yamaha Jubilo is a rugby union team based in Iwata, Shizuoka. The team came second behind Toshiba Brave Lupus in the second season of Japanese rugby's Top League. Wikipedia

Georgia national rugby union team.label: Georgia national rugby union team
Georgia national rugby union team.description: The Georgia national rugby union team represents Georgia in international rugby union. Rugby union in Georgia is administered by the Georgian Rugby Union. Wikipedia

Asociación Alumni.label: Asociación Alumni
Asociación Alumni.description: Asociación Alumni, usually just Alumni, is a rugby union and former football club located in Tortuguitas, Greater Buenos Aires, Argentina. Wikipedia

Bective Rangers.label: Bective Rangers
Bective Rangers.description: Bective Rangers is a rugby union club in Dublin, Ireland founded in 1881. The Club is affiliated to the Leinster Branch of the Irish Rugby Football Union and play in Division 2 of the All Ireland League. Wikipedia

Bedwas RFC.label: Bedwas RFC
Bedwas RFC.description: Bedwas RFC is a rugby union club located in the Welsh village of Bedwas. The club is a member of the Welsh Rugby Union and is a feeder club for Newport Gwent Dragons regional team. Wikipedia

Blackheath F.C..label: Blackheath F.C.
Blackheath F.C..description: Blackheath Football Club is a rugby football club based in Blackheath in south-east London, now playing at the Rectory Field. It was founded in 1858 and is the oldest open rugby club in the world. Wikipedia

Bridgend Ravens.label: Bridgend Ravens
Bridgend Ravens.description: Bridgend Ravens are a semi-professional rugby union club based in Bridgend, South Wales. They currently play in the Welsh Premier Division. Bridgend are a feeder club to the Ospreys regional team. Wikipedia

Cork Constitution.label: Cork Constitution
Cork Constitution.description: Cork Constitution is a Rugby Union club, based in Cork. It was founded by staff of the Cork Constitution. Since the paper did not publish on Sundays, the staff were looking for activities to pursue on Saturday afternoons. Wikipedia

Cross Keys RFC.label: Cross Keys RFC
Cross Keys RFC.description: Cross Keys RFC is a rugby union club located in the Welsh village of Crosskeys. The club is a member of the Welsh Rugby Union and is a feeder club for Newport Gwent Dragons regional team. Wikipedia

Connemara RFC.label: Connemara RFC
Connemara RFC.description: Connemara RFC is an Irish rugby team based in Clifden, Connacht. They play in Division 2B of the All-Ireland League. The club colour is all black, based on the colours of a popular fishing fly called the Connemara black. Wikipedia

Dolphin RFC.label: Dolphin RFC
Dolphin RFC.description: Dolphin Rugby Football Club is a rugby union club in Cork. It was founded in 1902, by members of Dolphin Swimming Club seeking to find a wintertime activity.They play in Division 1 of the All-Ireland League. Wikipedia

Dublin University Football Club.label: Dublin University Football Club
Dublin University Football Club.description: Dublin University Football Club is the rugby union club of the University of Dublin, Trinity College, in Dublin, Ireland. Wikipedia

Gala RFC.label: Gala RFC
Gala RFC.description: Gala Rugby Football Club is a rugby union team based in Galashiels in the Scottish Borders. Founded in 1875, it plays its home games at Netherdale. Wikipedia
